methods.name: getEstimatedProbability
methods.description:
The estimated probability that a given individual sharing these quasi-identifier values is in the dataset. This value, typically called δ, is the ratio between the number of records in the dataset with these quasi-identifier values, and the total number of individuals (inside and outside the dataset) with these quasi-identifier values.

For example, if there are 15 individuals in the dataset who share the same quasi-identifier values, and an estimated 100 people in the entire population with these values, then δ is 0.15.
